(1 comment)

GUARD partition is already part of 
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/+/52479
Done

If you're looking to save all the preserved partitions, they're listed in this pldm json file: https://github.com/openbmc/pldm/blob/master/oem/ibm/configurations/fileTable.json

Otherwise the title could be something like "Save specific preserved partitons", and describe why those were chosen to be part of the dump.

at present nick is looking for these https://w3.rchland.ibm.com/projects/bestquest/?defect=SW547550 
HBEL    (Hostboot error logs)  
HBD_FW  (Hostboot preserved attributes)
EECACHE (Hostboot VPD cache)

So saving these files 
HBEL - /media/hostfw/running/HBEL
EECACHE -  /media/hostfw/running/EECACHE

not sure which file to save for  (HBD_FW  (Hostboot preserved attributes)), is it all the files listed in the Json file? @adriana
Done
Any concerns about how much the size of the BMC dump would increase by?
I add these 3 partition files and the size of the BMC dump is less than 1MB after compression even though the original HBEL+HBD_RW+EEACHE was around 4.4mb.
requires more discussion

Also from an external user perspective, it may be surprising that a "bmc" dump contains "host firmware" data. There are already host dumps, including a hostboot type of dump, wouldn't it make more sense to leave host firmware data out of the bmc dump?

+1. Hostbootdump is packaged BMC  using custom tool opderport. These host specific data should be packaged as part of hostbootdump , by moving this plugins consumption to opdreport. 
Direction used is , BMC dump includes only BMC consumed host data ( DEVTREE/GUARD etc)  any other host specific data should packages respecting host type dumps.
Done

Reword it as,
openpower:dreport: save specific host firmware preserved partitions to the BMC dump
Done
Rename this to HBD_RW
Done
Please address the unresolved & new comments.

How we are triggering this plugin for the OpenPOWER-based systems? any impact on the less space OpenPOWER based system (I am referring to previous generation systems)?

(Looks, the added plugin is used to copy the PNOR partitions, and looks like a few partitions size more than 2MB)
Per the recently concluded internal design meeting discussions, the decision was to keep whatever that's required to aid in a field debug.

make the logic generic.
Keep the partion name in an array and loop through the array capture data , This approch will help to add any additional partition in future.
Done
